During a press briefing, White House Press Secretary Sarah Sanders discussed various topics including the President signing a bipartisan anti-sex trafficking bill, an executive order on reducing poverty in America, California Governor Jerry Brown sending National Guard members to help secure the southern border, and the ongoing situation in Syria. Sanders stated that the President holds Syria and Russia responsible for the chemical weapons attack in Syria and that all options are still on the table. She also addressed questions about the Mueller investigation and the possibility of direct military engagement with Russia. Sanders emphasized that the President believes a good relationship with Russia is good for the world but that Russia's actions and the investigation have hurt that relationship. She also mentioned that the President has had conversations with various world leaders and that all options, including diplomacy, are being considered in the case of Syria.